00:14:43.818 --> 00:14:45.319
I wrote him a letter.

245
00:14:46.621 --> 00:14:48.322
I sent it to the jail.

246
00:14:49.022 --> 00:14:50.224
Fan mail.

247
00:14:50.859 --> 00:14:52.359
Told him I liked his work.

248
00:14:53.994 --> 00:14:55.462
Go on.

249
00:14:56.196 --> 00:14:58.165
He ain't wrote back.

250
00:14:58.298 --> 00:15:00.668
I figured. hell. big shot
like him. he probably gets
a whole pile of them.

251
00:15:03.437 --> 00:15:05.406
But then two weeks ago.
he did write back.

252
00:15:05.540 --> 00:15:08.275
James Ulster's been dead
for nearly two months.

253
00:15:10.745 --> 00:15:12.346
That's what you think.

254
00:15:16.684 --> 00:15:18.285
What did the letter say?

255
00:15:20.087 --> 00:15:21.321
Jeb.

256
00:15:22.189 --> 00:15:24.425
Just instructions.

257
00:15:24.559 --> 00:15:26.193
Name. address.

258
00:15:27.027 --> 00:15:28.328
what to do to him.

259
00:15:29.296 --> 00:15:31.498
-You still have it?
-I burned it.

260
00:15:31.900 --> 00:15:33.434
Convenient.

261
00:15:34.234 --> 00:15:35.570
I got a letter.

262
00:15:36.236 --> 00:15:38.071
That's how he talked to me.

263
00:15:40.441 --> 00:15:44.244
- That's how he talked to all of us.
-  -"Us"?

264
00:15:45.012 --> 00:15:47.448
Who is "us." Jeb?

265
00:16:24.485 --> 00:16:25.687
Um... no.

266
00:16:28.690 --> 00:16:29.724
No. thank you.

267
00:16:34.896 --> 00:16:36.296
Come on. Trent.

268
00:16:38.867 --> 00:16:40.100
Live a little.

269
00:17:27.047 --> 00:17:28.816
Um...

270
00:17:30.552 --> 00:17:32.419
Uh. I'm sorry. Uh...

271
00:17:33.821 --> 00:17:35.055
Uh...

272
00:17:38.593 --> 00:17:41.863
Everyone here is just
so friendly.

273
00:17:42.897 --> 00:17:45.733
Well. I'm sure people
are friendly wherever you go.

274
00:17:48.603 --> 00:17:49.704
Hold still.

275
00:17:50.103 --> 00:17:52.540
- Oh.
- It's just a baby.

276
00:17:53.240 --> 00:17:55.108
You're not scared of spiders.
are you?

277
00:17:56.076 --> 00:17:57.679
No. no. No.

278
00:17:59.581 --> 00:18:00.515
No.

279
00:18:01.916 --> 00:18:04.117
<i>Call from Amanda.</i>

280
00:18:04.586 --> 00:18:06.821
<i>-Call from Amanda.</i>
-Oh. Excuse me.

281
00:18:08.088 --> 00:18:09.389
What do you got?

282
00:18:09.524 --> 00:18:11.593
Oswald just gave us
something concerning.

283
00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:13.528
He might not be acting alone.

284
00:18:14.028 --> 00:18:15.530
What'd he say?

285
00:18:15.663 --> 00:18:18.432
That someone calling themselves
Ulster sent him a letter.

286
00:18:18.566 --> 00:18:20.635
and he's not the only one
who got one.

287
00:18:21.069 --> 00:18:22.436
<i>Do you believe him?</i>

288
00:18:23.403 --> 00:18:24.606
<i>I don't know.</i>

289
00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:26.340
I have to go.

290
00:18:29.577 --> 00:18:30.344
Antonio!

291
00:18:30.477 --> 00:18:31.746
I'll check the back.

292
00:18:33.413 --> 00:18:34.816
Antonio!

293
00:18:38.118 --> 00:18:39.453
Antonio!

294
00:18:57.839 --> 00:19:00.108
Bedroom's clear.
I called for backup.

295
00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:01.643
Any sign of your uncle?

296
00:19:04.979 --> 00:19:06.346
He's gone.

297
00:19:15.389 --> 00:19:17.190
Have-Have you ever seen him?

298
00:19:17.659 --> 00:19:19.627
Um...

299
00:19:19.761 --> 00:19:21.829
This man...

300
00:19:21.963 --> 00:19:23.163
<i>No.</i>

301
00:19:23.798 --> 00:19:28.069
Will. Your Spanish.
Someone's
been practicing.

302
00:19:29.904 --> 00:19:32.974
What did you do?
What did you do. huh?

303
00:19:33.107 --> 00:19:34.642
Hey. hey. Easy.

304
00:19:36.978 --> 00:19:38.211
That's right.

305
00:19:38.946 --> 00:19:40.447
You work for me now.

306
00:19:40.581 --> 00:19:42.583
You're not Ulster. you're a...

307
00:19:43.951 --> 00:19:46.319
-You're an elf.
-What do you mean. an elf?

308
00:19:46.453 --> 00:19:48.455
You mean like a cool elf
with a bow and an arrow?

309
00:19:48.589 --> 00:19:50.625
No. you make cookies.
You live in a tree.

310
00:19:50.758 --> 00:19:52.492
I think you've finally lost
that marble.

311
00:19:52.627 --> 00:19:56.097
No. You're gonna help me
find my uncle.

312
00:19:56.229 --> 00:19:57.632
Agent Trent?

313
00:19:59.033 --> 00:20:00.500
Sorry to send you away.

314
00:20:00.635 --> 00:20:02.503
The local guys get testy
if it's an agent
they don't know.

315
00:20:02.637 --> 00:20:04.672
I-It's not my jurisdiction.
Understood.

316
00:20:04.806 --> 00:20:08.042
I have good news. though.
The warrant to track
Antonio's phone came through.

317
00:20:08.176 --> 00:20:10.812
I found him. He's on the move.
but he's not far.

318
00:20:12.379 --> 00:20:13.815
What's all that green?

319
00:20:23.591 --> 00:20:25.927
So...
...20 years with one person.

320
00:20:26.060 --> 00:20:29.496
then a four-month
ideal relationship
that you blew up on purpose.

321
00:20:29.630 --> 00:20:31.833
and now a situationship?

322
00:20:32.365 --> 00:20:35.603
You're missing
a little nuance. but yes.
those are the bullet points.

323
00:20:35.737 --> 00:20:37.304
How's the situationship going?

324
00:20:37.437 --> 00:20:40.273
It's great. You know.
we're kind of dating.

325
00:20:40.407 --> 00:20:41.776
There's nothing official.

326
00:20:41.909 --> 00:20:44.311
There are feelings.
but no commitment.

327
00:20:44.746 --> 00:20:47.215
And that's supposed to
make things less complicated?

328
00:20:47.582 --> 00:20:49.316
You know.
having no labels is wonderful.

329
00:20:49.449 --> 00:20:51.586
It's. uh. it's very liberating.

330
00:20:51.953 --> 00:20:53.487
Oh. Um...

331
00:20:54.555 --> 00:20:57.692
-That looks friendly.
-Don't worry.
it's not spider season.

332
00:20:58.826 --> 00:20:59.861
Right.

333
00:21:01.796 --> 00:21:05.265
Don't you wanna get married.
have kids and all that?

334
00:21:05.733 --> 00:21:08.268
Yes. I mean. you know.
when I meet the right person.

335
00:21:08.401 --> 00:21:10.470
How about you? You want kids?

336
00:21:12.673 --> 00:21:15.009
Very much so. Yeah.

337
00:21:18.411 --> 00:21:19.747
Oh. no.

338
00:21:20.515 --> 00:21:22.884
-What's wrong?
-I lost the signal.

339
00:21:23.316 --> 00:21:24.719
Let me try over here.

340
00:21:30.892 --> 00:21:32.492
Anything?

341
00:21:33.161 --> 00:21:35.495
No. Shoot.

342
00:21:35.630 --> 00:21:37.999
Let's just keep walking.

343
00:21:45.206 --> 00:21:46.439
I got you.

344
00:21:47.575 --> 00:21:49.376
-Leave the pack.
-No. the phone's in it.

345
00:21:49.510 --> 00:21:52.647
-We'll have
no way of tracking him.
-Elkie. you're slipping.

346
00:21:56.784 --> 00:21:59.053
-Grab my arm with both hands.
-But I...

347
00:21:59.187 --> 00:22:01.022
Do it.

348
00:22:01.155 --> 00:22:02.389
Elkie.

349
00:22:03.057 --> 00:22:04.826
Do it. Elkie.

350
00:22:08.529 --> 00:22:09.564
Okay.

351
00:22:25.279 --> 00:22:26.647
You okay?

352
00:22:27.380 --> 00:22:28.649
I'm okay.

353
00:22:31.219 --> 00:22:33.688
The phone.

354
00:22:34.255 --> 00:22:35.723
I'm so sorry. Agent Trent.

355
00:22:35.857 --> 00:22:39.961
Please. call me Will.

356
00:22:40.561 --> 00:22:41.796
Will.

357
00:22:51.739 --> 00:22:54.075
The good news is
I still have my phone.

358
00:22:54.809 --> 00:22:58.679
If we can get to an area
with reception. I can download
the tracking software.

359
00:22:59.412 --> 00:23:01.616
There's a signal tower
a few miles out.

360
00:23:02.049 --> 00:23:03.450
Well. let's get moving.

361
00:23:04.384 --> 00:23:05.485
-Thanks.
-Yeah.

362
00:23:10.791 --> 00:23:12.526
Tell me you hear that too.

363
00:23:34.815 --> 00:23:36.717
GBI. Anyone in there?

364
00:23:47.528 --> 00:23:48.930
What the hell?

365
00:24:03.077 --> 00:24:04.111
Mom.

366
00:24:54.095 --> 00:24:55.563
Will.

367
00:24:57.732 --> 00:24:59.033
What is it?

368
00:25:00.334 --> 00:25:01.902
It's a tape recorder.

369
00:25:04.739 --> 00:25:06.040
And a dummy.

370
00:25:09.343 --> 00:25:10.678
Antonio's phone.

371
00:25:11.212 --> 00:25:12.246
He was here.

372
00:25:12.713 --> 00:25:14.215
Now we can't track him.

373
00:25:47.281 --> 00:25:48.315
Do it again.

374
00:25:49.383 --> 00:25:51.118
This time with feeling.

375
00:25:57.091 --> 00:25:58.993
What did you just do?

376
00:25:59.126 --> 00:26:00.995
Who else knows about
the necklace?

377
00:26:01.128 --> 00:26:02.430
No.

378
00:26:02.563 --> 00:26:04.932
This is a bridge too far.

379
00:26:05.066 --> 00:26:06.467
-I will not--
-The necklace!

380
00:26:06.600 --> 00:26:07.802
Please.

381
00:26:08.269 --> 00:26:09.603
I may be flawed.

382
00:26:10.371 --> 00:26:11.572
But leave me my dignity.

383
00:26:11.705 --> 00:26:13.007
Fine.

384
00:26:15.709 --> 00:26:17.011
Start talking.

385
00:26:17.144 --> 00:26:18.712
Well. Lucy wasn't wearing it
when she died.

386
00:26:18.846 --> 00:26:21.282
Amanda found it
after she was abducted.

387
00:26:21.415 --> 00:26:22.850
Then she gave it to you. right?

388
00:26:22.983 --> 00:26:25.853
Which makes our suspect list
real short. You. me...

389
00:26:25.986 --> 00:26:27.354
Oh. wait a minute.

390
00:26:27.488 --> 00:26:29.790
What's Amanda's alibi
the night in question?

391
00:26:30.324 --> 00:26:32.059
What about
your little fan club. huh?

392
00:26:32.193 --> 00:26:34.161
The freaks you wrote to
from prison?

393
00:26:34.295 --> 00:26:36.730
Oh. you don't think
I'd tell those losers
stuff about my life.

394
00:26:36.864 --> 00:26:38.866
Jeb Oswald.

395
00:26:38.999 --> 00:26:41.469
That man shows his willy
to little girls. I'd like to
think I have some standards.

396
00:26:41.602 --> 00:26:44.772
You're right.
He's not your type at all.

397
00:26:44.905 --> 00:26:48.809
Exactly.
So. if I had nothing to do
with sending those letters...

398
00:26:49.944 --> 00:26:51.712
Then there's someone else
who knows

399
00:26:52.346 --> 00:26:54.315
about Antonio.
my mother. everything.

400
00:26:54.448 --> 00:26:56.317
This feels good. doesn't it?

401
00:26:56.450 --> 00:26:58.886
Tête-à-tête. After this.
let's go into Old San Juan.

402
00:26:59.019 --> 00:27:00.454
I know a place
we can throw back some rum.

403
00:27:00.589 --> 00:27:02.656
get in some real trouble.
That's what partners do.

404
00:27:02.790 --> 00:27:05.059
So how does whoever is
sending these letters
know details about my life?

405
00:27:05.192 --> 00:27:09.029
I never told anyone
about you. and I sure as hell
never mentioned Lucy.

406
00:27:09.163 --> 00:27:11.665
but you know me.

407
00:27:12.399 --> 00:27:17.171
There's nothing
I like more than savoring
the details of my own life.

408
00:27:19.807 --> 00:27:22.443
Eduardo. send a message
to Amanda Wagner.

409
00:27:22.577 --> 00:27:24.011
What if Ulster kept a journal?

410
00:27:24.145 --> 00:27:26.113
-Pfft.
-I know you tossed
his prison cell.

411
00:27:26.247 --> 00:27:28.749
but I think he's been
writing things down somewhere.

412
00:27:29.650 --> 00:27:31.085
Get a warrant if you have to.

413
00:27:32.486 --> 00:27:34.321
<i>Message sent.</i>

414
00:27:38.859 --> 00:27:40.094
I found this.

415
00:27:40.529 --> 00:27:41.762
It was under the bed.

416
00:27:47.835 --> 00:27:49.236
I heard you scream.

417
00:27:51.739 --> 00:27:53.374
My mother died like this.

418
00:27:54.408 --> 00:27:55.442
In childbirth?

419
00:27:57.411 --> 00:27:58.746
Jesus. Will.

420
00:28:00.014 --> 00:28:01.348
It's a setup.

421
00:28:02.149 --> 00:28:05.152
Someone took Antonio
to mess with me.
to get me out here.

422
00:28:05.853 --> 00:28:08.289
-I should have never
come to San Juan.
-This isn't your fault.

423
00:28:08.422 --> 00:28:09.490
None of it.

424
00:28:09.624 --> 00:28:11.926
Not Antonio. Not Lucy.

425
00:28:14.161 --> 00:28:15.196
Will.

426
00:28:15.896 --> 00:28:17.298
Your hand.

427
00:28:24.371 --> 00:28:25.406
There's something here.

428
00:28:26.307 --> 00:28:29.511
It's a message from Antonio.
Look.

429
00:28:30.010 --> 00:28:32.112
Why would he draw
a picture of a...

430
00:28:33.214 --> 00:28:35.149
<i>La Serpiente de Hierro.</i>

431
00:28:37.686 --> 00:28:39.053
The Iron Snake.

432
00:28:39.186 --> 00:28:41.422
It's an abandoned military base
way out in the jungle.

433
00:28:43.757 --> 00:28:45.893
- Will was right.
Ulster had a journal.
- Where is it?

434
00:28:46.026 --> 00:28:48.896
He gave it to his lawyer
to send to his next of kin
when he died.

435
00:28:49.029 --> 00:28:50.464
Next of kin. Who?

436
00:28:57.539 --> 00:28:58.739
Hello.

437
00:28:58.872 --> 00:29:00.274
<i>Ms. Trevens?</i>

438
00:29:01.475 --> 00:29:03.444
Yes.

439
00:29:03.578 --> 00:29:05.647
This is Special Agent
Faith Mitchell with the Georgia
Bureau of Investigation.

440
00:29:05.779 --> 00:29:08.749
I'd like to speak to
your daughter. Adelaide.
Is she available?

441
00:29:08.882 --> 00:29:11.385
She's not here.

442
00:29:12.386 --> 00:29:13.521
What's she done?

443
00:29:13.921 --> 00:29:17.992
Did you work as
James Ulster's secretary
from 1986 to 1989?

444
00:29:18.125 --> 00:29:21.362
I-I don't
remember the exact dates.

445
00:29:21.495 --> 00:29:23.130
What's this about?

446
00:29:23.264 --> 00:29:24.932
<i>Ms. Trevens. we spoke</i>
<i>to James Ulster's lawyer</i>

447
00:29:25.065 --> 00:29:26.333
<i>who confirmed that his effects.</i>

448
00:29:26.467 --> 00:29:28.402
including a journal
that he kept in prison.

449
00:29:28.536 --> 00:29:31.939
- was sent to his next of kin...
- ...your daughter.

450
00:29:32.507 --> 00:29:33.708
Wha...

451
00:29:33.841 --> 00:29:36.243
Ms. Trevens.
Amanda Wagner. GBI.

452
00:29:36.745 --> 00:29:40.715
Adelaide is James Ulster's
daughter. correct?

453
00:29:43.050 --> 00:29:45.587
James and I...

454
00:29:46.086 --> 00:29:48.623
It was just a onetime thing.

455
00:29:49.591 --> 00:29:51.693
<i>He wanted</i>
<i>nothing to do with her.</i>

456
00:29:52.226 --> 00:29:56.930
She wrote him letters.
hundreds of letters.

457
00:29:57.798 --> 00:30:00.367
Never once
did he write her back.

458
00:30:00.501 --> 00:30:04.004
He would never have
sent her anything.

459
00:30:04.706 --> 00:30:08.242
Even so. we'd still
like to speak to her.
Do you know where she is?

460
00:30:09.544 --> 00:30:11.579
She's visiting
her new girlfriend.

461
00:30:11.713 --> 00:30:13.682
Some woman she met online.

462
00:30:13.814 --> 00:30:15.583
- <i>Do you know</i> <i>that woman's name?
- </i> -I don't know.

463
00:30:15.717 --> 00:30:17.451
<i>I just know where she lives.</i>

464
00:30:17.585 --> 00:30:18.653
Where is that?

465
00:30:18.787 --> 00:30:21.523
San Juan. Puerto Rico.

466
00:30:33.901 --> 00:30:35.135
This is it.

467
00:30:43.877 --> 00:30:46.947
If Antonio's in there.
they must have found
another way inside.

468
00:30:59.460 --> 00:31:01.563
Looks like
an old sewer access.

469
00:31:02.062 --> 00:31:03.397
After you?

470
00:31:25.052 --> 00:31:26.588
What was that?

471
00:31:32.993 --> 00:31:35.095
Not spider season. huh?

472
00:31:36.865 --> 00:31:38.399
Are they poisonous?

473
00:31:38.833 --> 00:31:40.067
Very.

474
00:32:05.627 --> 00:32:08.362
Unbelievable. Battery died.

475
00:32:08.495 --> 00:32:10.397
-You have extras?
-Other pack.

476
00:32:12.132 --> 00:32:14.368
-Perfect.
-Here. give me the bag.

477
00:32:18.673 --> 00:32:19.707
What's that?

478
00:32:27.181 --> 00:32:29.450
Go. Go. go. go. go. go.

479
00:32:51.138 --> 00:32:54.709
Thank God for these sleeves.
You didn't get bitten. did you?

480
00:32:54.843 --> 00:32:56.578
I don't-I don't know.

481
00:32:59.848 --> 00:33:02.115
Okay. okay. Uh...

482
00:33:02.249 --> 00:33:03.518
Oh. One bite is okay.

483
00:33:03.651 --> 00:33:05.587
We just need to get you
to the hospital.

484
00:33:06.153 --> 00:33:07.622
We don't have time for that.

485
00:33:09.056 --> 00:33:10.290
Will. stop.

486
00:33:12.827 --> 00:33:14.161
What the--

487
00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:19.868
Oh. my God.

488
00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.703
What? What is it?

489
00:33:29.309 --> 00:33:31.613
This is it. Adelaide's
rental apartment.

490
00:33:34.816 --> 00:33:36.751
Adelaide Trevens! GBI!

491
00:33:54.334 --> 00:33:56.436
- Bedroom's clear.
- Hey. Faith.

492
00:33:57.137 --> 00:33:58.372
Check this out.

493
00:33:59.941 --> 00:34:01.141
It's Ulster's Journal.

494
00:34:01.275 --> 00:34:04.111
It has everything
about Will. Lucy.

495
00:34:04.679 --> 00:34:05.713
It's all here.

496
00:34:09.182 --> 00:34:11.519
- How bad is it?
- Bad.

497
00:34:12.119 --> 00:34:15.455
-Will it kill me?
-Yes. if you don't get
antivenom.

498
00:34:18.693 --> 00:34:19.627
How long?

499
00:34:19.761 --> 00:34:21.796
Ten hours. tops.

500
00:34:23.063 --> 00:34:24.197
Okay.

501
00:34:25.065 --> 00:34:28.368
Will. the more you move.
the faster the poison
will spread to your heart.

502
00:34:31.238 --> 00:34:32.472
Antonio.

503
00:34:33.841 --> 00:34:35.409
Antonio!

504
00:34:47.287 --> 00:34:48.422
Ormewood.

505
00:34:48.556 --> 00:34:49.724
Antonio.

506
00:34:53.561 --> 00:34:54.762
Antonio.

507
00:35:29.864 --> 00:35:31.131
Jesus.

508
00:35:33.467 --> 00:35:37.137
Whoo. whoo.

509
00:35:48.415 --> 00:35:50.585
Lana Elkie. FBI.

510
00:36:04.799 --> 00:36:06.534
I wasn't gonna
let him kill you.

511
00:36:11.839 --> 00:36:13.206
I wanna do that myself.

512
00:36:19.647 --> 00:36:21.348
Slide me your weapon.

513
00:36:32.259 --> 00:36:33.661
Cute.

514
00:36:34.227 --> 00:36:39.667
All these hours together
and I still have no idea
what my father saw in you.

515
00:36:40.467 --> 00:36:42.235
He never mentioned you.

516
00:36:43.671 --> 00:36:45.773
If I was a boy.
maybe he would have.

517
00:36:48.876 --> 00:36:50.878
I'm so much more like him
than you'll ever be.

518
00:36:51.012 --> 00:36:53.380
-Won't get any arguments
from me there.
-Stay where you are.

519
00:36:53.514 --> 00:36:55.850
-Where's my uncle?
-Guess you'll never know.

520
00:36:55.983 --> 00:36:57.652
Where is he?

521
00:36:57.785 --> 00:37:01.756
My dad spent
his last precious time
on Earth behind bars.

522
00:37:02.890 --> 00:37:05.760
-Now. you'll do the same.
-Oh. is that
what this is about?

523
00:37:06.326 --> 00:37:08.395
Huh? Revenge?

524
00:37:13.233 --> 00:37:14.602
What's wrong?

525
00:37:16.170 --> 00:37:17.772
You looking for these?

526
00:37:20.842 --> 00:37:23.544
I knew when you said her name.

527
00:37:24.812 --> 00:37:25.847
Lucy.

528
00:37:26.781 --> 00:37:28.549
I never told you her name.

529
00:37:30.551 --> 00:37:33.721
And yet you let me bring you
all the way out here.

530
00:37:33.855 --> 00:37:35.355
What can I say?

531
00:37:36.524 --> 00:37:37.992
I liked your company.

532
00:37:41.195 --> 00:37:42.830
Is he one of your pen pals?

533
00:37:43.564 --> 00:37:44.498
How many are there?

534
00:37:44.632 --> 00:37:46.500
Too many to count.

535
00:37:46.634 --> 00:37:50.605
Oh. but do they know it was you
they were talking to.

536
00:37:51.105 --> 00:37:52.874
and not your daddy?

537
00:37:54.341 --> 00:37:56.844
They would be so disappointed.

538
00:38:01.414 --> 00:38:02.750
Goodbye. Will Trent.

539
00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:21.102
Let me out. you son of a bitch!

540
00:38:21.235 --> 00:38:22.804
Let me out!

541
00:38:28.743 --> 00:38:30.678
I'm gonna kill you!

542
00:38:30.812 --> 00:38:34.314
No!

543
00:38:36.951 --> 00:38:38.385
Antonio!

544
00:38:40.588 --> 00:38:42.056
Damn you!

545
00:38:44.525 --> 00:38:45.927
Damn you!

546
00:38:51.464 --> 00:38:52.834
I'm gonna kill you!

547
00:39:02.677 --> 00:39:03.911
Oh. Okay.

548
00:39:06.346 --> 00:39:08.381
Jesus.
Be careful with that thing.

549
00:39:08.516 --> 00:39:10.218
-Oh. sorry.
-Okay.

550
00:39:10.350 --> 00:39:11.886
I hope this is right.

551
00:39:12.485 --> 00:39:14.454
Well. she had the map
at her place.

552
00:39:14.589 --> 00:39:16.524
unless she's into
tropical topography.

553
00:39:16.657 --> 00:39:19.060
Yeah. it should be
right around here.
but I don't see anything.

554
00:39:20.761 --> 00:39:22.563
Come on. Will. help us out.

555
00:39:23.331 --> 00:39:24.599
Will!

556
00:39:45.720 --> 00:39:48.022
Lay your head
on my lap. <i>Papito.</i>

557
00:39:48.488 --> 00:39:49.857
The ground is so hard.

558
00:39:51.424 --> 00:39:52.927
<i>Mmm.</i>

559
00:39:54.862 --> 00:39:56.764
Doesn't look good. does it?

560
00:39:56.898 --> 00:39:57.932
Shh.

561
00:39:59.133 --> 00:40:00.868
It'll all work out.

562
00:40:02.036 --> 00:40:04.705
Will we be together
on the other side?

563
00:40:04.839 --> 00:40:06.807
We're already together. <i>Papi.</i>

564
00:40:09.243 --> 00:40:10.711
We always have been.

565
00:40:14.115 --> 00:40:16.117
I wanted more than this.

566
00:40:21.188 --> 00:40:22.890
I wanted a family.

567
00:40:26.127 --> 00:40:27.962
Then scream. Will.

568
00:40:29.363 --> 00:40:30.698
<i>Scream.</i>

569
00:40:49.083 --> 00:40:50.450
Will?

570
00:40:50.952 --> 00:40:51.953
Will?

571
00:40:54.355 --> 00:40:55.589
Faith.

572
00:40:56.557 --> 00:40:57.490
Will. Will.

573
00:40:57.625 --> 00:40:59.026
-Call a medevac.
-Yeah.

574
00:41:00.895 --> 00:41:03.898
Get me a priority medevac.
I'm sending the coordinates
right now.

575
00:41:04.532 --> 00:41:05.933
What happened?

576
00:41:06.067 --> 00:41:07.201
Spiders.

577
00:41:07.335 --> 00:41:08.736
Poison.

578
00:41:09.870 --> 00:41:11.572
She's in the cell.

579
00:41:11.706 --> 00:41:14.608
Ulster's daughter.
She knows where my uncle is.

580
00:41:15.209 --> 00:41:17.845
Go. go. It's okay.
It's gonna be okay.

581
00:41:17.979 --> 00:41:20.214
- Stay with me.
- Adelaide?

582
00:41:40.001 --> 00:41:41.035
Adelaide?

583
00:42:06.961 --> 00:42:09.263
Hey. hey.
Will. Will. stay with me.

584
00:42:09.397 --> 00:42:10.531
Help is on the way. okay?

585
00:42:10.664 --> 00:42:12.133
-What'd she say?
-She wasn't there.

586
00:42:12.266 --> 00:42:14.735
I searched
the whole place. Will.

587
00:42:15.469 --> 00:42:17.705
I'm sorry. bud. She's gone.

588
00:42:18.272 --> 00:42:21.876
Stay with me.
Hey. hey. Will? Will?

589
00:42:22.009 --> 00:42:23.911
Will. stay with me.

589
00:42:24.305 --> 00:43:24.167
